Among the hills to the E. of Lahr lay the strong castle of Geroldseck on the Schonbe1g, dominating the upper waters of the Schutter to its w. and the Kinzig on its E. The situation of all three is carefully described in a letter from Ottelinus of Lahr to Beatus Rhenanus, 27 Feb. 1531 (BRE. 272 ; but on p. 383. 31 for occidentem read orientem).

Conrad Frick († 3 April 1535) was elected Abbot of Schuttern on 12 J uly 1518: but not much is known of him. In Feb. 1522 he was visiting Nuremberg (ZE. 266). In 1523 he was present at the election of an abbot for the Benedictine house of Alpirsbach‚ high up in the valley of the Kinzig (GC. v. 1065). Luscinius (Ep. 302. 1611) speaks of him as an old friend and tells a story of his humour in letting a house in Strasburg (Ioci αο sales. Augsburg, S. Ruff, 13 Feb. 1524, 110. 82). In May 1525 he took up arms with the nobles for the suppression of the Peasants (ZE. 243), and in April 1526 was negotiating with the Austrian autho- rities at Ensisheim for the restoration of the monks of Hiigshofen (BRE. 255).
